We are the Grijalva family and here is our story how we became @haulin_thefamily 

We had recently moved to a new city, and didn’t really know anybody. And then year 2020 happened and with everyone wanting to social distance, it got harder to make friends. We had just had another baby and had no family close by other than Brian’s twin brother and family that lived near us for only a week after we moved to ATL area. They had a plan set in place to full time travel. We had said that lifestyle wasn’t for us but after watching their travel adventures for 2 years it inspired us to do the same. 

Before kids we traveled a lot and we missed it. We’ve always been interested in owning an RV for vacationing and started looking at them when our oldest son was an infant. Our mindset quickly shifted when Brian was let go from his job in December 2020. Since nothing was holding us back from living full time on the road, we decided to leave the excuses and fears behind us. We sold our house, cars, had multiple yard sales (we accumulated a ton of stuff after 10 years of marriage and 3 kids😅) and everything fell into place for our family to move forward with this travel lifestyle.

It’s given us the opportunity to see friends and family around the US that we otherwise would have not been able to see more than once a year. It’s also brought forever friendships into our lives.

We have not looked back at our old life but instead look forward to continuing to build on all the amazing memories from these last 2.5 years on the road. This life is a special gift we’ve been given and we live each day with the intent of never wasting it. 

Thank you for being here and continuing to follow our life on the road! Your support means so much. ❤️

People ask us if we miss having a house. There are days we miss having more space (Brian currently works out of his truck) but other than that, we don’t miss having a house.

Having a house requires more cleaning, house upkeep and having to buy more “stuff” to fill rooms so they aren’t empty. It’s never ending and was way more stressful on me then how we are living now. With tiny living I can have our home cleaned and organized in an hour. We do 1-2 small loads of laundry a day and load the dishwasher at night. Having less stuff and less square footage means less responsibility and fewer chores. Perspective changes quick with tiny living.

Once you find your groove with this lifestyle (took us 3 months) you realize the highs FAR outweigh the lows.

Could you see yourself selling it all to travel full time in an RV? Do you know anyone considering this lifestyle? *Share this reel to help inspire.

Follow along 👉🏼@haulin_thefamily 💙

RV home renovation | Tiny living renovation | RV slide renovation | tiny living family | DIY home renovations

WE DID IT! 💪🏼 Here is how we renovated our RV living room to feel more like a home. It’s been a slowww 2 month process of gradually renovating…
✔️removed original furniture
✔️tore out cabinets and window valances 
✔️filled in holes, sanded, primed & painted walls
✔️ripped up carpet, installed carpet tiles
✔️installed new roller shades, curtain, shelving, speaker holders and furniture.
None of which is easy to do when you’re also living in the RV with little ones.

Special shout-out to @recpro for designing this super comfy, lightweight leather recliner loveseat that fit this space PERFECTLY! 🥰 My son said it was his favorite part of our remodel. Use code HAULIN to $ave when you shop with them!

Other items can be found in our Amazon storefront under “Interior Home Design”. 

Would you like to see more videos on the breakdown of this renovation? Which part of this remodel was your favorite? 

And lastly thanks to Stacy @sealovehome for making our tiny home smell incredible with her toxin-free candles. Looks so cute on our living room shelf!! Use code Kam10 to $ave!

Life sure is filled with unexpected twists and turns isn’t it? We had this fabulous idea we’d be on the road for a few years seeing all the things, exploring all the places, collecting countless memories with our kids and then …we got hit with a ton of unexpected costs which made us stop and reevaluate our travel plans. Throughout our journey we’ve been embracing the unpredictability of this lifestyle, and our family has developed the skill to adapt quickly and pivot when needed. It can be both challenging (mentally and emotionally) and rewarding (with opportunities for growth as a family, as a couple and personally).

So for now we are stationed in southern California. Embracing the good and the bad and next year… well… we shall see where we end up. 😉

How to switch things up from RVing full time? Plan an adults only get-away weekend by dropping the kids off with family. We try to do this once a month as a couple and feel that it’s important to continue to date even after you’re married.

I had been counting down the days beyond excited to go see Sebastian Maniscalco LIVE because he is my all time FAVORITE comedian. 😂 We sat in the 3rd row and my face literally hurt from laughing so much! We had never been to nor heard of Funner CA where the show was held. There wasn’t much else to do in the area other than enjoy the resorts. The resorts had plenty of entertainment and delicious restaurants to choose from (even got to hear @koolandthegang concert at our resort after we got back from the comedy show). Can’t wait to have more date weekends like this one. Worth every penny!

Thankful for our big, crazy California family!

🥹 As our family embarked on this thrilling journey of full-time RV travel 2.5 years ago, little did we anticipate the rollercoaster of challenges awaiting us. The initial vision of years filled with exploration and adventure was quickly met with many unexpected repairs and maintenance hurdles. We faced RV issues before we even got on the road (🥹) and from there it did not stop! This isn’t uncommon.

But despite the unforeseen obstacles, our decision to do this holds no regret. 🥰 Throughout our journey we got to visit 26 states, reconnected with old friends and family around the country, and made new lifelong friends we likely would not have met otherwise. 

The invaluable growth and profound shifts in perspective we've encountered along the way have rendered every challenge worthwhile.❤️

Beyond the repairs, we've felt a deeper family bond and gained a newfound clarity on how we aspire to shape our lives.

We leave full time RV travel behind us with the hopes now of international travel in our future, the kids focusing on developing their passions (⚾️🎨🎹) and skillsets and exploring Southern California where we now happily reside. 🫶🏼🙌🏼✈️ 

>>Thank you as always for your continued support and love 💙@haulin_thefamily
